title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H2 – Apr 22 2022
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H2 – Apr 22 2022
description:
A taste of upcoming liberal "dirty tricks": Democrats try to disqualify Congresswoman Marjorie Taylor Greene from running for reelection. Clay says, "If she committed a crime, then charge her with a crime -- and, by the way, if she's charged with a crime, she could still run." Fauci insists the CDC should be above federal courts: "We are concerned about courts getting involved in things that are unequivocally a public health decision. This is a CDC issue." Ian Miller, author of Unmasked: The Global Failure of COVID Mask Mandates, joins Clay and Buck to discuss the covid and mask mandate madness, including constant flip-flops by major cities.

Follow Clay & Buck on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/c/clayandbuck
